</head>");				 NewWindow.document.write ("<body bgcolor='black' background='");				 NewWindow.document.write (theBg);				 NewWindow.document.write ("' style='background-repeat:no-repeat;'");				 NewWindow.document.write (" leftmargin='0' topmargin='0' marginwidth='0' marginheight='0'>");				 NewWindow.document.write ("<table align='center'><tr>");				 NewWindow.document.write ("<td align='center' valign='top' height='");				 NewWindow.document.write (tableHeight);				 NewWindow.document.write ("'>");				 NewWindow.document.write ("&nbsp;<br></td></tr></table>");				 NewWindow.document.write ("</body></html>");				 NewWindow.document.close();			}		</script></head><body>	<div id="container"><?php include("menu.php") ?>        <div id="content">				<table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=5>            	<tr><td><h2>Description</h2></td><td></td></tr>					<tr>						<td valign="top" align="right"><strong>Overview:</strong></td>						<td>							Emote is a small structure that a person can crawl into and sit							inside.  Once a person is inside, the exterior of the structure will							begin to vibrate and move.  The structure will change form to							reflect the emotional state of the person.  When the person							exits the structure the exterior will stop changing.  The							structure will not change until another person enters it.						</td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td valign="top" align="right"><strong>Emotions:</strong></td>						<td>							Initially the structure will be able to reflect joy,							sadness and anger to begin but eventually we would like to							find ways to express more types of emotion.							<p><i>Joy:</i>								<br>								<nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/joy_front.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Joy Front');">									<img src="images/thumb_joy_front.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/joy_per.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Joy Perspective');">									<img src="images/thumb_joy_per.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br><nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/joy_side.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Joy Front');">									<img src="images/thumb_joy_side.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/joy_env.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Joy Environment');">									<img src="images/thumb_joy_env.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br>							</p>							<p><i>Anger:</i>								<br>								<nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/anger_front.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Anger Front');">									<img src="images/thumb_anger_front.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/anger_per.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Anger Perspective');">									<img src="images/thumb_anger_per.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br><nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/anger_side.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Anger Front');">									<img src="images/thumb_anger_side.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/anger_env.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Anger Environment');">									<img src="images/thumb_anger_env.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br>							</p>							<p><i>Sadness:</i>								<br>								<nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sadness_front.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Sadness Front');">									<img src="images/thumb_sadness_front.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sadness_per.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Sadness Perspective');">									<img src="images/thumb_sadness_per.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br><nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sadness_side.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Sadness Front');">									<img src="images/thumb_sadness_side.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sadness_env.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Sadness Environment');">									<img src="images/thumb_sadness_env.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br>							</p>						</td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td valign="top" align="right"><strong>Interaction:</strong></td>						<td>							When a person is inside the structure they will be able to interact							with a touch-screen computer.  The person will be presented with							questions that they will answer by touching one of several possible							answers displayed on the touch screen.  A computer will extract							emotional information from this interaction and trigger changes in							the exterior structure of the building accordingly.						</td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td valign="top" align="right"><strong>Exterior:</strong></td>						<td>							The exterior of the structure will be made up of movable, color							changing "feathers" and retractable "quills".  The "quills" will							extend when the mood is angry and will retract otherwise.							The color, motion and orientation of the "feathers" will							also reflect the mood.  If the person is angry then the							"feathers" will extend outward become hot colored and move							jerkily, if the person is sad the "feathers" will become							closed, cold colored and move very little, and if the							person is happy the "feathers" will become open, warm							colored and move calmly.  							<br><br>Here are <em><font color = "#006699">two rough animations</font></em> of the device							transforming between different emotional states (both are							.mov files, the first one is 32M and the second one is							6.5M):								<br><br>								<nobr>									<a href="AniBg01.mov">									<img src="images/AniBg01.jpg"></a>									<a href="AniNoBg.mov">									<img src="images/AniNoBg.jpg"></a>								</nobr>						</td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td valign="top" align="right"><strong>Interior:</strong></td>						<td>							The interior of the structure/animal, is intended to be a							place where a person will feel comfortable expressing							themselves.  It will be a meditative space.  The whole							interior will be like a large reclining chair that is							covered with a soft							<a href="http://www.foamorder.com/memory.html" target="nw">"memory foam"</a> 							material that will form to the body of the person.  There							will be small windows on the ceiling that will provide a							little bit of light but additional light, should the user							want it, will be provided by two small adjustable electric							lights.  Speakers will be embedded in the walls which will							provide audio feedback relating to the touch-screen							computer interaction as well as soothing sounds to							reenforce the meditative environment.							<br><br>							Like the exterior of the structure, the interior of the							sturcture will react to the person inside.  The seat will							form to the person's body and there will be small vibrators							embedded in the seat that will massage the person,							providing physical consolation.  The sound environment will							also play a role in this consolation.  The person should							exit the structure at ease, having expressed their							emotions, feeling positive.						</td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td valign="top" align="right"></td>						<td>								<br>								<nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sideHeart01.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Side View');">									<img src="images/thumb_sideHeart01.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sideHeart02.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Side View');">									<img src="images/thumb_sideHeart02.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br><nobr>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/sideHeart03.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Side View');">									<img src="images/thumb_sideHeart03.jpg"></a>									<a href="javascript:OpWin('images/per04.jpg',640,480,0,0,0,'Perspective with Person');">									<img src="images/thumb_per04.jpg"></a>								</nobr>								<br>						</td>					</tr>				</table>        </div>	</div>	<br><br></body></html>